  url		= {http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/1984A%26A...132..389P},
  abstract	= {The authors give a mean {UV} extinction curve for the
		  Small Magellanic Cloud which corresponds to the most common
		  case and consequently to the most probable typical
		  extinction law. The curve is almost linear in lambda-1
		  without any evidence of the 2200 Å galactic feature. This
		  is consistent with almost pure silicate interstellar grains
		  and little graphite grains, as expected from the large
		  underabundance of carbon in the {SMC} with respect to other
		  heavy elements.},
